	<p class="lead" ><b>Curse of Naxxramas</b></p>
</div>

<br><br><br>

<div class="jumbotron">
	<p>Set in the Scourge necropolis of Naxxramas, Curse of Naxxramas will be a five-wing adventure, with each wing representing one of the wings of the World of Warcraft Naxxramas raid instance. The adventure will feature a total of 30 new cards, gained through completing various aspects of the adventure. 

The Curse of Naxxramas Adventure was released on July 22, 2014. The launch event which gave players the Arachnid Quarter for free ended on September 30, 2014.</p>
</div>	

<br><br><br>

<div class="jumbotron">
	<div id="struc"></div>
	<p class="lead" ><b>Naxxramas Pricing Structure</b></p>
	<p>The Curse of Naxxramas adventure is a paid content addition to Hearthstone; It may be purchased by using the in-game currency gold or real money.

The adventure is divided into 5 different wings, and each wing will cost 700 gold or $6.99 USD. Don't worry though, if you pay using real money and you buy wings in bulk, each wing will only cost $5 USD.

Below is a table of pricing costs by currency for the Naxxramas adventure. Please note that there are no package deals available for gold purchased, but they have been included for comparisons sake.</p>
	<img class="img-responsive" src="images/Aventures/prixnaxx.png" alt="Prix">
</div>
<br><br><br>

<div class="jumbotron">
	<div id="quartier"></div>
	<p class="lead" ><b>New Cards!</b></p>
	<p>Curse of Naxxramas will be introducing thirty new cards to the game; This includes both class and neutral cards. These cards are only obtained while completing specific tasks in the adventure itself and cannot be opened up from booster packs like the previous Expert set. Cards are earned by:</p>
	<li>Defeating Bosses (15 Cards)</li>
	<li>Finishing Wings (6 Legendary Cards)</li>
	<li>Completing Class Challenges (9 Cards)</li>
	<p>These cards are not craftable and cannot be disenchanted for dust, much like the Basic set.</p>
</div>
<br><br><br>

<div class="jumbotron">
	<div id="newcards"></div>
	<p class="lead" ><b>Class Cards</b></p>
	<p>Nine of the new cards will be class specific, one for each class. These cards are obtained from Class Challenges.</p>
	<img class="img-responsive" src="images/Aventures/cartenaxx.png" alt="Prix">
</div>
<br><br><br>

